        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:29PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Amma, or 11 miles south of Spencer, moving north
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ripley, Spencer, Sissonville, Sandyville, Kenna, Amma, Reedy, Statts
Mills, Harmony, Tariff, Kentuck, Walton, Left Hand, Looneyville,
Annamoriah, Leroy, Fairplain, Gay, and Gandeeville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 between mile markers 21 and 29.
Interstate 77 in West Virginia between mile markers 114 and 133,
between mile markers 139 and 140, and between mile markers 144 and
148.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
